164
00:12:48,685 --> 00:12:50,006
I made that choice again,

165
00:12:50,006 --> 00:12:53,988
and that's what makes me different from other professionals.

166
00:12:56,167 --> 00:12:57,888
So while moving forward in a quest,

167
00:12:57,888 --> 00:13:00,610
there are times when you want to change your mind as a player

168
00:13:00,610 --> 00:13:02,192
and not follow that quest.

169
00:13:02,192 --> 00:13:04,614
And however, most games, when you do that,

170
00:13:04,614 --> 00:13:06,055
it just equals a failure.

171
00:13:06,055 --> 00:13:07,216
You failed on that quest.

172
00:13:07,216 --> 00:13:09,097
That's the standard game flow.

173
00:13:09,097 --> 00:13:10,959
But for Deadly Premonition, we thought

174
00:13:10,959 --> 00:13:13,481
that should be allowed as a player's decision.

175
00:13:13,481 --> 00:13:16,143
And so we spent some time making an extra branch

176
00:13:16,143 --> 00:13:18,385
so that the player can have that as an option.

177
00:13:18,385 --> 00:13:21,167
This allowed players to feel better

178
00:13:21,167 --> 00:13:22,728
about taking a break from the game,

179
00:13:22,728 --> 00:13:25,871
and this allowance of a change of heart, if you will.

180
00:13:26,287 --> 00:13:43,517
makes the player feel more comfortable, and once they are comfortable, they are more willing to cooperate with the story.

181
00:13:43,517 --> 00:13:55,604
There are times when you just want to do something else in the game, but if that causes a failure, you feel so constricted.

